Windows Server 2022 — Domain Controller Configuration

Complete setup for Windows Server 2022 as the domain controller managing corp.local domain.


Installation & Network Setup

Create the VM


Name: DC01
RAM: 4096 MB
CPU: 2 cores
Disk: 60 GB
Network: Host-only Adapter → vboxnet0


Boot from Windows Server 2022 ISO, select Desktop Experience edition, and complete installation. Set Administrator password and rename computer to DC01.

Configure Static IP Address

The domain controller must have a fixed IP — if it changes, the entire domain breaks.

powershellNew-NetIPAddress -InterfaceAlias Ethernet -IPAddress 192.168.10.10 -PrefixLength 24 -DefaultGateway 192.168.10.1

Set DNS to point to itself (DC01 becomes the DNS server after AD install):

powershellSet-DnsClientServerAddress -InterfaceAlias Ethernet -ServerAddresses 127.0.0.1

Add default route for internet traffic:

powershellNew-NetRoute -DestinationPrefix 0.0.0.0/0 -NextHop 192.168.10.1 -InterfaceAlias Ethernet -RouteMetric 256

Verify Network Connectivity

Test connectivity to pfSense:

powershellping 192.168.10.1

Test internet connectivity:

powershellping 8.8.8.8

Both must succeed before proceeding.


Install Active Directory Domain Services

Install AD DS Role

Open PowerShell as Administrator:

powershellInstall-WindowsFeature -Name AD-Domain-Services -IncludeManagementTools

This installs Active Directory Domain Services and management tools. Expect "Success: True" output after 2-3 minutes.

Promote to Domain Controller

powershellInstall-ADDSForest -DomainName corp.local -SafeModeAdministratorPassword (ConvertTo-SecureString "Lab@Secure2024!" -AsPlainText -Force) -Force -NoRebootOnCompletion

Creates new Active Directory forest corp.local and promotes DC01 to domain controller. Takes 3-5 minutes. Warnings about DNS delegation are normal.

Restart Server

powershellRestart-Computer

Server reboots and loads all Active Directory services.

Verify Active Directory

After reboot:

powershellGet-ADDomain

Expected output shows:


Name: corp — domain short name
Forest: corp.local — full domain name
PDCEmulator: DC01.corp.local — DC01 is primary controller
DomainMode: Windows2016Domain — domain functional level



Create Active Directory Structure

Create Organizational Units

powershellNew-ADOrganizationalUnit -Name "Staff" -Path "DC=corp,DC=local"
New-ADOrganizationalUnit -Name "IT_Admins" -Path "DC=corp,DC=local"

OUs are folders that organize users and computers by department.

Create User Accounts

John Smith:

powershellNew-ADUser -Name "John Smith" -GivenName "John" -Surname "Smith" -SamAccountName "jsmith" -UserPrincipalName "jsmith@corp.local" -Path "OU=Staff,DC=corp,DC=local" -AccountPassword (ConvertTo-SecureString "UserPass@123" -AsPlainText -Force) -Enabled $true

Amy Jones:

powershellNew-ADUser -Name "Amy Jones" -GivenName "Amy" -Surname "Jones" -SamAccountName "ajones" -UserPrincipalName "ajones@corp.local" -Path "OU=Staff,DC=corp,DC=local" -AccountPassword (ConvertTo-SecureString "UserPass@123" -AsPlainText -Force) -Enabled $true

Bob Wilson:

powershellNew-ADUser -Name "Bob Wilson" -GivenName "Bob" -Surname "Wilson" -SamAccountName "bwilson" -UserPrincipalName "bwilson@corp.local" -Path "OU=Staff,DC=corp,DC=local" -AccountPassword (ConvertTo-SecureString "UserPass@123" -AsPlainText -Force) -Enabled $true

Create Security Group

powershellNew-ADGroup -Name "Domain_Staff" -SamAccountName "Domain_Staff" -GroupCategory Security -GroupScope Global -Path "OU=Staff,DC=corp,DC=local"

Add Users to Group

powershellAdd-ADGroupMember -Identity "Domain_Staff" -Members "jsmith", "ajones", "bwilson"


Verification

List All OUs

powershellGet-ADOrganizationalUnit -Filter "Name -like '*'"

Returns: Staff, IT_Admins

List Users in Staff OU

powershellGet-ADUser -Filter "Name -like '*'" -SearchBase "OU=Staff,DC=corp,DC=local"

Returns: jsmith, ajones, bwilson with full details

List Group Members

powershellGet-ADGroupMember -Identity "Domain_Staff"

Returns: All three users with their details


Key Configuration Details

Static IP: 192.168.10.10/24 ensures DC01 is always reachable

DNS: Set to 127.0.0.1 (itself) so DC01 is authoritative for corp.local

Gateway: 192.168.10.1 points to pfSense for internet routing

Domain: corp.local is the top-level domain that all machines join

Users: All three users can log into domain-joined machines using their credentials


What This Server Does


Active Directory — manages user accounts, computers, groups, and policies for the entire domain
DNS Server — resolves corp.local hostnames and forwards external queries to internet
DHCP Relay — works with pfSense to assign IP addresses to network machines


This is the central management point for the entire lab network.


Troubleshooting

Can't ping pfSense after static IP configuration:

powershellNew-NetRoute -DestinationPrefix 0.0.0.0/0 -NextHop 192.168.10.1 -InterfaceAlias Ethernet -RouteMetric 256

Need to run commands as Administrator:
Right-click PowerShell → "Run as Administrator"

Verify domain joined machine can reach DC:

powershellping dc01.corp.local
